OL,3,CPalestinian filmmaker wins LGBTQ+ film
OL,4,Cfestival
OL,6,FFormer Plaid Cymru leader, Adam Price
OL,7,Fwas a judge at the festival. He
OL,8,Fdescribed the winning film as "an
OL,9,Fimportant reminder that queer people
OL,10,Fexist everywhere, including in
OL,11,FPalestine at a time of war and
OL,12,Foccupation."
OL,14,FThe judges commended the winning film
OL,15,Ffor "its amazing acting and direction".
OL,17,FThe Iris Film Festival is held in
OL,18,FCardiff every year and is the largest
OL,19,FLGBTQ+ film festival in the world.
